**Copyright (C) 2026 The Hub Studio. All Rights Reserved.**

Project PHDE is an infrastructure technology developed by The Hub Studio. To maximize community adoption while strictly protecting the integrity of our architecture, this software is released under a **Dual-Licensing Model**. 

By default, download, usage, or modification of this source code binds you to one of the two licensing pathways outlined below.

---

## 1. The Dual-License Dual Tracks

### Track A: Open-Source Community Edition (GNU AGPLv3)
For open-source developers, hobbyists, academic researchers, and compliance-aligned systems, PHDE is available under the **GNU Affero General Public License version 3 (AGPLv3)**. 

*   **The Network Copyleft Trigger:** Under Section 13 of the AGPLv3, if you modify PHDE and host it on a server to offer network services (Software-as-a-Service, Cloud API, or remote indexing), you **must** make your complete, modified source code publicly available under the terms of the AGPLv3.
*   The complete text of the AGPLv3 can be found in the accompanying `LICENSE-AGPL.txt` file in this repository.

### Track B: Enterprise Commercial Edition (Proprietary)
For corporations, proprietary SaaS providers, embedded hardware OEMs, and teams unable or unwilling to expose their application architecture under copyleft terms, The Hub Studio offers a traditional commercial license.

*   This track grants you the legal right to run PHDE inside closed-source cloud platforms, private enterprise architectures, or distributed consumer hardware devices without triggering the public disclosure requirements of the AGPLv3.
*   For commercial licensing inquiries, terms, or procurement options, contact: `licensing@thehubstudio.com`

---

## 2. Team Membership & Automatic CLA Assent

To maintain absolute legal hygiene and ensure that The Hub Studio retains the uncompromised right to commercialize and dual-license the Project, all development contributions are governed by our **Contributor License Agreement (CLA)**.

> ### ⚠️ Automatic Agreement Clause for Team Members and Contributors
> 
> By accepting an official invitation to join the PHDE GitHub Organization, joining the project's core development team, executing a code commit directly to the official repository branches, or submitting a Pull Request, **you explicitly, irrevocably, and automatically agree to the full terms of the PHDE Individual Contributor License Agreement (CLA).**
>
> This contribution model functions as an implied-in-fact contract. **No physical signature or separate digital document execution is required.** 
>
> Your explicit actions of joining the team or submitting intellectual property to our repository constitute complete assent to the CLA terms, granting The Hub Studio a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, irrevocable license to distribute and commercialize your contributions under both our Open-Source and Proprietary tracks.

If you do not agree to the terms of the CLA, do not accept a team invitation, do not push code to this repository, and do not submit pull requests.

---

## 3. Reviewing the CLA Terms
For transparency, the exact terms of the agreement you automatically accept upon contributing or joining the team are detailed in the `CLA.md` file located in the root directory of this repository.
